│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The core issue is a crash in `getSpillCost` due to a null `SpillPlacementBB`. My previous attempts to fix this in `getTreeCost` by returning an invalid cost when `SpillPlacementBB` is  │
│ null have led to widespread test regressions. This indicates that while the fix prevents the crash, it makes the vectorizer too conservative, preventing it from vectorizing code it     │
│ otherwise should.                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem lies in the assumption that if `MustSpill` is true, a spill location must be found. When `getSpillPlacementBlock` returns null (as it does for the reproducer IR containing  │
│ a function argument), my previous fixes would invalidate the entire vectorization candidate. The regressions suggest this is the wrong approach. The vectorizer should be able to        │
│ proceed even if a spill location isn't immediately found.                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The most direct and least disruptive fix is to make `getSpillCost` robust against a null `SpillPlacementBB`. If `SpillPlacementBB` is null, it means no spill location could be          │
│ determined. In this scenario, the cost of spilling is effectively zero because no spill can be inserted. The function should simply return a zero cost. This prevents the crash without  │
│ pessimistically blocking vectorization, allowing the rest of the cost model to make the final decision. This minimal change should fix the crash without causing the regressions.        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify `getSpillCost` to check if `SpillPlacementBB` is null and return zero if it is.                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/BasicBlock \*BB = SpillPlacementBB;/a \  if (!BB)\n    return 0;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
